olic drink per day. Patients should be advised to seek medical attention if they experience potential signs and symptoms of hepatotoxicity such as fever, rash, itching, anorexia, nausea, vomiting, fatigue, malaise, right upper quadrant pain, dark urine, pale stools, and jaundice.', 'Synergism', 'Caution is advised if lomitapide is used with other potentially hepatotoxic agents (e.', 'Major', 'pharmacodynamic', NULL, 'https://ddinter2.scbdd.com/server/interact/118980/', '[1] "Product Information. Juxtapid (lomitapide)." Aegerion Pharmaceuticals Inc, Cambridge, MA.[2] "Product Information. Juxtapid (lomitapide)." Aegerion Pharmaceuticals Inc, Cambridge, MA.', 'Pertuzumab, Cetuximab, Avelumab, Panitumumab, Obinutuzumab, Bevacizumab, Necitumumab, Dostarlimab, Ramucirumab, Atezolizumab, Amivantamab, More', 'Gemfibrozil, Fenofibric acid, Evinacumab, Evolocumab, Probucol, Dextrothyroxine, Cholestyramine, Ezetimibe, Clofibrate, Colestipol, Niacin, More', 1767369485);
